# OpenObserve HA project context

## Repo

- **HACS integration**: `custom_components/openobserve/` (domain `openobserve`, v0.1.2+)
- **Supervisor add-on** (HA OS only): `openobserve_log_shipper/` (Fluent Bit → `/_multi`)
- **Docker test deploy**: `deploy/docker/run.sh` or `deploy/portainer/run-containers.sh`

## Architecture

| Piece | Runs in container HA? | Ingest |
|-------|---------------------|--------|
| Integration | Yes | `POST /api/{org}/{stream}/_json` (JSON array) |
| Log shipper add-on | No (needs Supervisor) | `/_multi` NDJSON |

Default streams: `home_assistant_logs`, `home_assistant_events`. Batching: **50 records** or **5s** flush (options).

## Docker (local test)

```bash
export ZO_ROOT_USER_PASSWORD='...'
./deploy/docker/run.sh
```

- OpenObserve: http://localhost:5080
- HA: http://localhost:8123
- **Integration base URL must be** `http://openobserve:5080` (service name), not `localhost`

Bind-mount: `custom_components/openobserve` → `/config/custom_components/openobserve`.

## OpenObserve auth

`ZO_ROOT_USER_EMAIL` / `ZO_ROOT_USER_PASSWORD` apply **only on first boot** with an **empty** data volume. Changing env later does not reset password — delete volume `openobserve-data` and recreate.

## Config flow (HA 2025.12+)

`OpenObserveOptionsFlowHandler` must **not** assign `self.config_entry` (read-only). Use `self._config_entry` in `__init__`; do **not** call `super().__init__(config_entry)` (raises `TypeError`).

Setup schema: all fields use `TextSelector`, not bare `str`.

## Production LAN

User also runs OpenObserve at `http://10.20.0.54:5080` (org `default`). Credentials live in local gitignored rules, not in repo.

## Icons

Brand assets from [Dashboard Icons `open-observe`](https://dashboardicons.com/icons/open-observe) (homarr-labs/dashboard-icons, Apache-2.0). HACS validate uses `ignore: brands`.

## HACS

`hacs.json`, hassfest + hacs/action in `.github/workflows/validate.yaml`. Publish: `Shaffer-Softworks/home-assistant-openobserve`.
